{"title_page": "Savoie's 4th constituency", "text_new": "{{short description|Constituency of the French Fifth Republic}}\n{{Infobox French constituency\n| name                = 4th Constituency of [[Savoie]]\n| image               = File:MapOfSavoies4thConstituency.png|thumb|MapOfSavoies4thConstituency\n| caption             = Savoie's 4th Constituency shown within [[Savoie]].\n| member-type         = Deputy\n| member              = [[Patrick Mignola]] <ref name=\"assemblee-nationale.fr\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/qui|title=577 D\u00e9put\u00e9s - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr}}</ref>\n| party-colour        = MoDem\n| member-party        = [[Democratic Movement (France)|MoDem]]\n| department          = [[Savoie]]\n| region              = \n| canton              = Chamb\u00e9ry Est, Chamb\u00e9ry Nord, Chamb\u00e9ry Sud, Chamb\u00e9ry Sud-Ouest, Le Ch\u00e2telard, Cognin, Gr\u00e9sy-sur-Is\u00e8re, Saint-Alban-Leysse, Saint-Pierre-d'Albigny\n| census-date         = 2017\n| Voters              = 74639 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/elections/carte/2017/resultats|title=Les r\u00e9sultats aux \u00e9lections l\u00e9gislatives de 2017 - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe 4th constituency of the [[Savoie]] ([[French language|French]]: ''Quatri\u00e8me circonscription de la Savoie'') is a French legislative [[Constituency (France)|constituency]] in the Savoie ''[[Departments of France|d\u00e9partement]]''. Like the other 576 French constituencies, it elects one [[National Assembly of France|MP]] using the [[First-past-the-post voting|first past the post]] election system with a run-off.\n\n==Description==\n\nThe 4th constituency of [[Savoie]] was created in 2012 as a result of the [[2010 redistricting of French legislative constituencies]]. The consists of [[Chamb\u00e9ry]] and some of its immediate hinterland in the north east of the department.\n\nThe constituency initially elected a [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]] deputy but she failed to win reelection in the face of [[Emmanuel Macron|Emmanuel Macron's]] centrist coalition in 2017.<ref>http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/elections/circonscription/2017/resultats/73/04</ref>\n\n==Assembly Members==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Election !! Member !! Party\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Socialist Party (France)/meta/color}}\" | || [[2012 French legislative election|2012]] || [[Bernadette Laclais]]||[[Socialist Party (France)|PS]]\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Movement (France)/meta/color}}\" | || [[2017 French legislative election|2017]] || [[Patrick Mignola]]||[[Democratic Movement (France)|MoDem]]\n|}\n\n<ref name=\"assemblee-nationale.fr\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{French National Assembly constituencies}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:French legislative constituencies of Savoie|4]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Constituency of the French Fifth Republic}}\n{{Infobox French constituency\n| name                = 4th Constituency of [[Savoie]]\n| image               = File:MapOfSavoies4thConstituency.png|thumb|MapOfSavoies4thConstituency\n| caption             = Savoie's 4th Constituency shown within [[Savoie]].\n| member-type         = Deputy\n| member              = [[Patrick Mignola]] <ref name=\"assemblee-nationale.fr\">{{cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/qui|title=577 D\u00e9put\u00e9s - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr}}</ref>\n| party-colour        = MoDem\n| member-party        = [[Democratic Movement (France)|MoDem]]\n| department          = [[Savoie]]\n| region              = \n| canton              = Chamb\u00e9ry Est, Chamb\u00e9ry Nord, Chamb\u00e9ry Sud, Chamb\u00e9ry Sud-Ouest, Le Ch\u00e2telard, Cognin, Gr\u00e9sy-sur-Is\u00e8re, Saint-Alban-Leysse, Saint-Pierre-d'Albigny\n| census-date         = 2017\n| Voters              = 74639 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/elections/carte/2017/resultats|title=Les r\u00e9sultats aux \u00e9lections l\u00e9gislatives de 2017 - Assembl\u00e9e nationale|website=www2.assemblee-nationale.fr}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe 4th constituency of the [[Savoie]] ([[French language|French]]: ''Quatri\u00e8me circonscription de la Savoie'') is a French legislative [[Constituency (France)|constituency]] in the Savoie ''[[Departments of France|d\u00e9partement]]''. Like the other 576 French constituencies, it elects one [[National Assembly of France|MP]] using the [[First-past-the-post voting|first past the post]] election system with a run-off.\n\n==Description==\n\nThe 4th constituency of [[Savoie]] was created in 2012 as a result of the [[2010 redistricting of French legislative constituencies]]. The consists of [[Chamb\u00e9ry]] and some of its immediate hinterland in the north east of the department.\n\nThe constituency initially elected a [[Socialist Party (France)|Socialist Party]] deputy but she failed to win reelection in the face of [[Emmanuel Macron|Emmanuel Macron's]] centrist coalition in 2017.<ref>http://www2.assemblee-nationale.fr/elections/circonscription/2017/resultats/73/04</ref>\n\n==Assembly Members==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Election !! Member !! Party\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Socialist Party (France)/meta/color}}\" | || [[2012 French legislative election|2012]] || [[Bernadette Laclais]]||[[Socialist Party (France)|PS]]\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Democratic Movement (France)/meta/color}}\" | || [[2017 French legislative election|2017]] || [[Patrick Mignola]]||[[Democratic Movement (France)|MoDem]]\n|}\n\n<ref name=\"assemblee-nationale.fr\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n\n{{French National Assembly constituencies}}\n\n[[Category:French legislative constituencies of Savoie|4]]\n", "name_user": "Rich Farmbrough", "label": "safe"